The paper focuses on the analysis and development of beaconless georouting protocols in distributed wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of analytical tools and strategies for improving the performance of these protocols, which could fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the comparison of different georouting protocols for different application scenarios, which could fall under the categories of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and systems and control (cs.SY).
